27. si moriatur] Barbirius⁷ account of the position is given in Ep. 1245. 4—21 : that in order to save expense at Rome he had made an informal arrangement there about the payments to be made to Erasmus 3 but that if 110 should die before Erasmus, the necessary bulls could be obtained from Rome without further difficulty than the defrayal of the regular official charges. If Erasmus should die first, these charges would be avoided.

54. Traiectum superiorem] From the mention of Limburg, evidently Maas- tricht, the ‘ upper serry ’ as compared With Utrecht‚ ‘ the lower '. The note from the margin of E quoted in Ep. 867. 161n appears therefore to contain a misprint‚ inferius for superius (cf. Ep. 1022. 26, where Horawitz read τῖη for su). I cannot find any serry on the Meuse above Maastricht to substantiate the note in E.
